Cashew e Pepe e Funghi                     df, vegan
  --America's Test Kitchen
  
1/2 c roasted cashews
1/4 c nutritional yeast
2 tbsp white miso
1/2 tsp table salt, + salt for cooking pasta
1/4 c evoo
6 oz oyster mushrooms, trimmed and chopped
5 garlic cloves, sliced thin
1 tsp coarsely ground pepper
1 lb spaghetti
2 tbsp chopped fresh parsley
1 tsp lemon juice

Process cashews in blender on low speed until consistency of fine gravel mixed with sand, 10-15 s. Add 1 1/2 c water, nutritional yeast, miso, and salt and process on low speed until combined, ~5 s. Scrape down sides of blender jar and let mixture sit for 15 min. Process on low speed until all ingredients are well blended, ~1 min. Scrape down sides of blender jar, then process on high speed until sauce is completely smooth, 3-4 min. Heat oil in 12" skillet over medium-high heat until shimmering. Add mushrooms and cook until deep golden brown and crispy, 7-10 min. Off heat, stir in garlic and pepper and cook using residual heat of skillet until fragrant, ~1 min. Meanwhile, bring 4 qt water to boil in large pot. Add pasta and 1 tbsp salt and cook, stirring often, until al dente. Reserve 1/2 c cooking water, then drain pasta and return it to pot. Add sauce, mushroom mixture, parsley, and lemon juice to pasta and toss until sauce is thickened slightly and pasta is well coated, ~1 min. Before serving, adjust consistency with reserved cooking water as needed and season with salt and pepper to taste.


Notes: The sauce can be made and stored in the fridge for up to a week. 
